*: {{rhymes|eɪʃən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{obsolete}} [[acceptance]]; reception; favorable reception or regard; state of being [[acceptable]].
#:* This is saying worthy of all '''acceptation'''. - ''1 Timothy 1:15''
#:* Some things ... are notwithstanding of so great dignity and '''acceptation''' with God. - [[w:Richard Hooker|Richard Hooker]].
# The meaning in which a word or expression is [[understood]], or generally received; as, term is to be used according to its usual ''acceptation''.
#:* My words, in common '''acceptation''', Could never give this provocation. - [[w:John Gay|John Gay]]

